.TH ALARM 1
.SH NAME
alarm \- ask for delayed note
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B alarm
[
.I time
.I path
.I arg
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Alarm
causes an
.B alarm
note (see
.IR notify (2))
to be sent to the process indicated by the argument
.I path
after the number of seconds
given by the argument
.I time.
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/alarm.c
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR sleep (2)
